parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected activation of the automatic emergency braking system can cause the vehicle to jolt to a stop, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control, especially if other vehicles are following closely.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or brakes without warning
the automatic braking system activates without any obstruction or warning
the vehicle jolts to a stop
and the system beeps or alerts the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, including the braking system, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The malfunction light comes on
the crash sensor fails
the wipers come on randomly
the cruise control stops working
and the shift system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver seat electric motor can cause the seat to become stuck in a position, potentially leading to a loss of control or accident, especially if the driver is unable to reach the pedals.
symptoms: The driver seat electric motor fails
the seat cannot move forward or back
and the seat becomes stuck in a position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear liftgate can cause the door to close unexpectedly, potentially striking occupants or objects, leading to injuries or damage.
symptoms: The rear liftgate closes unexpectedly
the door strikes occupants or objects
and the door does not stop or open automatically when detecting an object in its path.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Backup Camera and Navigation System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera and navigation system can cause the driver to lose visibility and situational awareness, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The backup camera and navigation screen go blank
the driver cannot use the backup camera
and the system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine noise and performance issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even die on the highway, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: Roaring noise from the engine
engine RPM goes high but car struggles to speed up
humming sound
knocking sound
rough idling
and sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning cooling fan can cause excessive noise, overheating, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Loud fan noise
fan stays on for an extended period
and repeated instances of fan malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission issues can cause the vehicle to struggle to accelerate, lose power, and potentially lead to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: Engine RPM goes high but car struggles to speed up
vehicle feels like slowing down
and sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause the vehicle to die on the highway, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: Engine failure
throwing a rod
and requiring a complete new engine replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to unexpected shifts, loss of power, and inability to shift into gear, which can increase the risk of accidents and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may hesitate or refuse to shift into gear
the transmission may slip or hesitate when shifting
the vehicle may lose power or stall
the transmission may unexpectedly shift into neutral
the vehicle may be unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, increasing the risk of accidents and leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may hesitate or refuse to shift into gear
the transmission may slip or hesitate when shifting
the vehicle may lose power or stall
the transmission may unexpectedly shift into neutral
the vehicle may be unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECU can cause a range of issues, including transmission problems, audio system malfunctions, and safety feature failures, which can increase the risk of accidents and compromise the overall safety and performance of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience issues with the transmission
audio system
lane departure warning
collision warning
heated/cooled seats
infotainment system
and other electronic systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the automatic emergency braking system can cause sudden and unexpected stops, which can lead to rear-end collisions, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly and unexpectedly stops or slows down without any obstacles or vehicles in front
the automatic braking system warning lights or messages appear on the dashboard
the vehicle's brakes are applied without driver input
the vehicle's speed is suddenly reduced without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unwanted Activation of Forward Collision Avoidance System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected activation of the forward collision avoidance system can cause the vehicle to brake suddenly, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions, accidents, and injuries to occupants and other road users.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly and unexpectedly applies the brakes
often at high speeds
without any obstacle or vehicle in front of it; the warning lights on the dashboard illuminate; the brakes engage
and the vehicle comes to a sudden stop.
